<subSubSection id="055796C77BB56A786BB85F40571E9D6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B8FC0CA97D2241547FD5581DE1EC6B61" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AEF468D6E50AE4FDEA3B7C64EE40647D" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
The species name is from the Latin 
<emphasis id="968C40A3D1C5A670BC57B9E620F863E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">maculatus</emphasis>
(spotted), referring to the wing pattern.
</paragraph>
